oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:title: White-tailed deer
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:description: Black and white photograph of a Virginia white-tailed deer in captivity near park headquarters at Gatlinburg. The deer has a large set of antlers and is standing in front of a cluster of trees.

It was found as a helpless fawn and raised in captivity. These deer, natives of the Great Smokies, had almost been driven from the area before the park's establishment. The few that are left are supplemented from a nearby National Forest.
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:source: Tennessee Department of Conservation Photograph Collection, 1937-1976
